document_metadata.name: The O-GlcNAc modification protects against protein misfolding and aggregation in neurodegenerative disease

citation.name: ACS chemical neuroscience
citation.title: O-GlcNAc Modification Protects against Protein Misfolding and Aggregation in Neurodegenerative Disease.

links.evidence: The addition and removal of OGlcNAc onto protein substrates is governed entirely by two ubiquitously expressed enzymes: O-GlcNAc transferase [EC 2.4.1.255] (OGT) and O-GlcNAc hydrolase [EC 3.2.1.169] (OGA) respectively (see Figure 2).
